text: The Idaho Falls City Office Building is a historic building in Idaho Falls, Idaho. It was built in 1929-1930 as a rectangular structure with "double fluted Ionic columns," reminiscent of Beaux-Arts architecture. With It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since August 30, 1984. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Bonneville County, Idaho Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1929 Category:1929 establishments in Idaho
title: Idaho Falls City Building
